{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"reedy-hew-plume","description":"## Why\n\nA re-fired container review re-litigates delivered AC (false BLOCKs / stale coaching). We need a\ndeterministic gate that drops those findings without hiding anything live — mirroring the novelty\nfloor (ADR 0008) and drift-refresh (ADR 0002).\n\n## What\n\nAdd a third Pass-3 floor in `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py` (`pass3_decide`) that, using the\ncompletion sub-answers (story: Pass-2 sub-call) and the delivered-now predicate (story:\ndelivered-now), DROPS a finding iff ALL hold: attribution = a delivered-now child AND\ncontainment = limited-to-closed AND layer = plan-semantics AND priority (validity x impact) < floor\nAND criterion not in {security, contract}. Recompute every run (never persist a drop). Record each\ndrop to the `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar (`sidecar.py`) joinable by finding id. Gate behind a\n`verify.completion_floor_active` evidence flag + a `verify.completion_priority_floor` in\n`src/rebar/config.py` (VerifyConfig), defaulting inert — the total back-out, exactly like the\nnovelty flags.\n\n## Scope\n\n- IN: the Pass-3 drop predicate; the config keys; sidecar `floored` recording; the deterministic\n  aggregation of the three sub-answers + priority + structural criterion class.\n- OUT: the sub-questions themselves (separate story); the delivered-now predicate (separate story).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `pass3_decide` drops iff attribution=delivered-now AND containment=limited AND layer=plan-semantics AND priority<floor AND criterion not in {security,contract}; all other combinations keep.\n- [ ] Suppression is inert unless `verify.completion_floor_active` is true; `verify.completion_priority_floor` is configurable (mirrors `novelty_priority_floor`).\n- [ ] Every drop is written to the `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar (joinable by finding id) and is recomputed each run (no persisted suppression).\n- [ ] A blocking security/contract-criterion finding is never dropped regardless of the other axes.\n- [ ] Unit tests cover the truth table (each single-condition flip preserves the finding).","id":"6533-d3cc-7ffa-4d67","parent_id":"66ac-fd03-6d4d-4249","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Pass-3 completion floor: deterministic drop of delivered re-litigation + config evidence-gate"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782973220687195001,"uuid":"607fe866-9686-4dfe-a5c3-4e0ad00cda04"}